{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "web:first-corinthians.11",
    "translationId": "web",
    "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
    "chapterNumber": 11,
    "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 11",
    "summary": "Source text for 1 Corinthians 11 in World English Bible."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.11.1",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 11:1",
      "text": "Be imitators of me, even as I also am of Christ.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.11.2",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 11:2",
      "text": "Now I praise you, brothers, that you remember me in all things, and hold firm the traditions, even as I delivered them to you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.11.3",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 11:3",
      "text": "But I would have you know that the head of every man is Christ, and the head of the woman is man, and the head of Christ is God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.11.4",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 11:4",
      "text": "Every man praying or prophesying, having his head covered, dishonors his head.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.11.5",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 11:5",
      "text": "But every woman praying or prophesying with her head uncovered dishonors her head. For it is one and the same thing as if she were shaved.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.11.6",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 11:6",
      "text": "For if a woman is not covered, let her hair also be cut off. But if it is shameful for a woman to have her hair cut off or be shaved, let her be covered.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.11.7",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 11:7",
      "text": "For a man indeed ought not to have his head covered, because he is the image and glory of God, but the woman is the glory of the man.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.11.8",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 11:8",
      "text": "For man is not from woman, but woman from man;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.11.9",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 11:9",
      "text": "for man wasn’ t created for the woman, but woman for the man.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.11.10",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 11:10",
      "text": "For this cause the woman ought to have authority over her own head, because of the angels.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.11.11",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 11:11",
      "text": "Nevertheless, neither is the woman independent of the man, nor the man independent of the woman, in the Lord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.11.12",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 11:12",
      "text": "For as woman came from man, so a man also comes through a woman; but all things are from God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.11.13",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 11:13",
      "text": "Judge for yourselves. Is it appropriate that a woman pray to God unveiled?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.11.14",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 11:14",
      "text": "Doesn’ t even nature itself teach you that if a man has long hair, it is a dishonor to him?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.11.15",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 11:15",
      "text": "But if a woman has long hair, it is a glory to her, for her hair is given to her for a covering.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.11.16",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 11:16",
      "text": "But if any man seems to be contentious, we have no such custom, neither do God ’ s assemblies.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.11.17",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 11:17",
      "text": "But in giving you this command I don’ t praise you, because you come together not for the better but for the worse.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.11.18",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 11:18",
      "text": "For first of all, when you come together in the assembly, I hear that divisions exist among you, and I partly believe it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.11.19",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 11:19",
      "text": "For there also must be factions among you, that those who are approved may be revealed among you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.11.20",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 11:20",
      "text": "When therefore you assemble yourselves together, it is not the Lord ’s supper that you eat.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.11.21",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 11:21",
      "text": "For in your eating each one takes his own supper first. One is hungry, and another is drunken.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.11.22",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 11:22",
      "text": "What, don’ t you have houses to eat and to drink in? Or do you despise God ’ s assembly and put them to shame who don’ t have enough? What shall I tell you? Shall I praise you? In this I don’ t praise you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.11.23",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 11:23",
      "text": "For I received from the Lord that which also I delivered to you, that the Lord Jesus on the night in which he was betrayed took bread.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.11.24",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 11:24",
      "text": "When he had given thanks, he broke it and said, “ Take, eat. This is my body, which is broken for you. Do this in memory of me.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.11.25",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 11:25",
      "text": "In the same way he also took the cup after supper, saying, “ This cup is the new covenant in my blood. Do this, as often as you drink, in memory of me.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.11.26",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 11:26",
      "text": "For as often as you eat this bread and drink this cup, you proclaim the Lord ’ s death until he comes.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.11.27",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 11:27",
      "text": "Therefore whoever eats this bread or drinks the Lord ’ s cup in a way unworthy of the Lord will be guilty of the body and the blood of the Lord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.11.28",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 11:28",
      "text": "But let a man examine himself, and so let him eat of the bread and drink of the cup.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.11.29",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 11:29",
      "text": "For he who eats and drinks in an unworthy way eats and drinks judgment to himself if he doesn’ t discern the Lord ’s body.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.11.30",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 11:30",
      "text": "For this cause many among you are weak and sickly, and not a few sleep.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.11.31",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 11:31",
      "text": "For if we discerned ourselves, we wouldn’t be judged.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.11.32",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 11:32",
      "text": "But when we are judged, we are disciplined by the Lord, that we may not be condemned with the world.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.11.33",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 11:33",
      "text": "Therefore, my brothers, when you come together to eat, wait for one another.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:first-corinthians.11.34",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "first-corinthians",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Corinthians 11:34",
      "text": "But if anyone is hungry, let him eat at home, lest your coming together be for judgment. The rest I will set in order whenever I come.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
